ECONOMY AWARDS IN NOBEL

The Economic Sciences in Nobel 2019
  Abhijit Banerjee, Esther Duflo and Michael Kremer 
    "for their experimental approach to alleviating global poverty"


The Economic Sciences in Nobel 2018
  William D. Nordhaus 
    "for integrating climate change into long-run macroeconomic analysis"
  Paul M. Romer 
    "for integrating technological innovations into long-run macroeconomic analysis"


The Economic Sciences in Nobel 2017
  Richard H. Thaler 
    "for his contributions to behavioural economics"
  Cashless society
  Kumarhane fişleri, kredi kartları ile harcamak daha kolaydır. Nakitle ödeme yaparkenki acı. 
  MIT prof. Prelec deneyi - the psychology of spending. The pleasure of buying from the pain of paying
